```from fastapi import FastAPI, File, UploadFile

app = FastAPI()

@app.post("/image")
async def image(image: UploadFile = File(...)):
    return {"filename": image.filename}

```

I expect that you will find that the time to send an image to FastAPI will be > 50ms.   It is easier to scale the number of images that can be processed but you will find that the latency may be far too much for you.

Best of luck!

